INSERT INTO `ym_translations` VALUES ('3600', '{{class_category_file_links}}', '337', 'summary', 'en', 'Word Formation Class\r\n\r\nOne of the biggest problems every IELTS, TOEFL, and GRE candidate faces is the issue of vocabulary. It will not be an exaggeration if one says that the task of learning vocabularies is so formidable that many candidates have no choice except shying away from or postponing the exam. However, there are some ways which are able to reduce the amount of challenge for the candidates, and one of the best ones is learning words through word formation. The syllabus proposed by Avaye Shahir Institute is a shortcut to internalize 1,200 English words in just eight sessions. A simple look at the syllabus makes it clear that the sample words indicated are not easy and can challenge any candidate. Nonetheless, instead of demotivating the learners, the trainer has arranged them in a way that they can make learning experience a fascinating and constructive effort. Each session is divided into three parts: the focus in the first part is on prefixes and suffixes alongside main ideas. The second and third part are arranged harmoniously to cover a broad range of vocabularies without threatening the curiosity of the learners. There is also a section devised in the second group that considers English words borrowed from other languages. It should be mentioned that the candidates can cover 10 vocabularies derived from every word; that means, they learn 150 words in each session. There are also some exercises accompanied by the term pamphlet to assist the candidates to internalize the words effectively and efficiently.\r\nHossein Khezerlou');
